WEBVTT

00:40.457 --> 00:43.543
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, GROUPS, AND
ORGANIZATIONS IN THIS WORK ARE FICTITIOUS

00:43.626 --> 00:46.379
SCENES WITH ANIMALS ARE STAGED
ACCORDING TO ANIMAL WELFARE GUIDELINES

00:46.463 --> 00:48.673
MYEONGJU STATION

00:48.757 --> 00:49.966
Yeo-reum, let's just go.

00:50.049 --> 00:51.926
We're going to end up missing the train.

00:52.635 --> 00:54.179
Let's just wait a little longer.

00:54.763 --> 00:58.141
When I called him earlier,
he said he was almost here.

00:58.224 --> 01:00.018
But it's been 30 minutes already.

01:00.101 --> 01:01.770
He probably just left his house.

01:02.937 --> 01:03.980
We'll just run for it.

01:04.064 --> 01:05.523
Yeo-reum, Bom!

01:06.066 --> 01:07.442
-Jae-hun!
-Hey!

01:07.525 --> 01:08.359
Hey!

01:08.443 --> 01:10.320
Stop wasting time
and get over here already!

01:10.403 --> 01:11.654
Run faster!

01:11.738 --> 01:13.031
You punk.

01:13.531 --> 01:14.783
Dae-bum?

01:15.742 --> 01:17.452
-Jae-hun!
-I thought he couldn't…

01:18.078 --> 01:19.329
Yeo-reum.

01:20.330 --> 01:22.332
You were waiting for Dae-bum, weren't you?

01:22.415 --> 01:25.084
That's not true.
I had no idea he was coming.

01:25.168 --> 01:26.377
You had no idea?

01:27.462 --> 01:29.255
-Get over here.
-Hey.

01:29.339 --> 01:31.299
-Let's hurry.
-Come on.

01:31.382 --> 01:32.801
MYEONGJU STATION

01:32.884 --> 01:34.844
-The train is here!
-Let's hurry!

01:34.928 --> 01:37.555
-We're going to miss it!
-Gosh.

01:37.639 --> 01:38.932
Watch out.

01:39.015 --> 01:41.684
-Let's hop on.
-Come on!

01:43.645 --> 01:46.105
We almost missed the train because of you.

01:46.189 --> 01:47.524
Sorry, I was…

01:48.191 --> 01:49.567
boiling these.

01:49.651 --> 01:50.819
You brought eggs?

01:50.902 --> 01:52.403
What are you, an old lady?

01:52.487 --> 01:55.281
Did you bring Dae-bum with you?

01:55.824 --> 01:56.658
No.

01:56.741 --> 01:58.284
I met him on my way here.

01:59.160 --> 02:01.412
I didn't know you were coming.

02:03.414 --> 02:04.916
What do you mean you didn't know?

02:04.999 --> 02:06.209
Are you sure you didn't?

02:06.292 --> 02:08.336
You didn't even refund his ticket.

02:10.213 --> 02:11.381
Did you bring salt too?

02:23.810 --> 02:26.813
-It's so beautiful here.
-Everything is green.

02:29.065 --> 02:30.358
DONGCHEON

02:30.441 --> 02:32.819
-We're here already?
-Hey, Jae-hun.

02:32.902 --> 02:34.529
How do you sleep the entire way here?

02:34.612 --> 02:37.198
I stayed up preparing the food for today.

02:38.158 --> 02:38.992
Yeo-reum.

02:39.075 --> 02:40.952
How long do we have to walk from here?

02:41.035 --> 02:43.413
It's just a 35-minute walk from here.

02:44.038 --> 02:45.623
You looked into it already?

02:45.707 --> 02:48.209
He's the best. Then shall we go?

02:48.293 --> 02:50.086
-Sure.
-It's so far away.

02:50.169 --> 02:53.339
Gosh, it is quite far.
When are we going to get there?

02:55.633 --> 02:57.135
Hold on.

02:59.137 --> 03:00.096
What's wrong?

03:00.889 --> 03:02.307
We're missing a suitcase.

03:02.390 --> 03:04.058
-What?
-It's not with you, Dae-bum?

03:04.934 --> 03:06.978
A suitcase? What are you talking about?

03:07.061 --> 03:08.438
You're the one who brought it.

03:10.064 --> 03:11.524
The bus!

03:12.025 --> 03:13.401
Mister!

03:14.611 --> 03:15.612
Mister!

03:16.779 --> 03:19.115
-Sir!
-How can he forget about his luggage?

03:27.916 --> 03:30.543
-Can't I get it any sooner?
-This place is so beautiful.

03:30.627 --> 03:31.878
Okay.

03:31.961 --> 03:33.004
This is great.

03:33.796 --> 03:35.882
I can get my luggage back
tomorrow morning.

03:35.965 --> 03:37.717
Hey, it's fine. We have another suitcase.

03:37.800 --> 03:39.302
We can share the food in there.

03:39.886 --> 03:42.013
I only brought cooking tools in there.

03:42.096 --> 03:43.181
What?

03:43.264 --> 03:44.432
So we have to starve?

03:44.515 --> 03:47.435
You should have told us earlier.

03:47.518 --> 03:48.436
It's okay.

03:49.020 --> 03:51.522
I brought some ramyeon just in case.

03:51.606 --> 03:52.899
I brought something too.

03:54.150 --> 03:55.235
Apples.

03:55.777 --> 03:56.778
No.

03:56.861 --> 03:58.112
-Both of you, stop.
-Hey.

03:58.696 --> 04:01.241
What should we do then?
I don't want to starve.

04:02.575 --> 04:03.618
Wait.

04:12.293 --> 04:14.712
How did you think to pick peaches?

04:15.296 --> 04:16.798
You're so resourceful.

04:17.382 --> 04:20.677
Wherever I go,
I can get food in exchange for work.

04:22.470 --> 04:24.097
You're putting me to shame, Bom.

04:26.015 --> 04:28.226
I heard there was a storm coming,
so I was worried.

04:28.309 --> 04:30.061
It's good that you came when you did.

04:31.229 --> 04:35.149
Can you pick the ones
that are smaller first?

04:35.233 --> 04:36.359
-Sure.
-Okay.

04:38.319 --> 04:42.282
Goodness. That young man over there
is such a great worker.

04:43.449 --> 04:45.159
You've made my day. You know what?

04:45.243 --> 04:47.370
How about some Korean chicken
as compensation?

04:47.453 --> 04:49.247
-Really?
-Seriously?

04:49.330 --> 04:51.207
I feel so much more energetic

04:51.291 --> 04:53.501
with all of you youngsters around.

04:55.128 --> 04:57.255
-Thank you, sir.
-Thank you.

04:57.839 --> 05:00.049
-Yes, I can't wait!
-I can't wait.

05:04.971 --> 05:06.222
-Dad.
-Yes?

05:06.306 --> 05:08.308
You should dress up like that every day.

05:08.391 --> 05:09.517
Why?

05:10.184 --> 05:11.269
Do I look good?

05:11.352 --> 05:13.021
You look rich.

05:13.104 --> 05:15.481
Hey, I don't have to dress up
like this to be rich.

05:15.565 --> 05:17.942
I'm just too busy to be playing dress-up.

05:18.026 --> 05:20.028
Then why are you
dressed up like that today?

05:20.111 --> 05:21.654
That's not for you to know.

05:22.613 --> 05:23.740
Look at you.

05:24.449 --> 05:25.908
Where do you think you're going?

05:25.992 --> 05:27.952
I have an important appointment today.

05:28.036 --> 05:31.539
Appointment, my foot.
All you do is laze around at home.

05:31.622 --> 05:32.999
It's hot today, isn't it?

05:34.542 --> 05:35.501
Hey.

05:35.585 --> 05:38.379
Are you going out to meet a girl?

05:39.130 --> 05:40.214
Gosh.

05:40.715 --> 05:43.259
Why would you ask me that?

05:43.342 --> 05:45.178
Can't I have some privacy around here?

05:45.261 --> 05:47.221
Privacy? Goodness sake.

05:47.305 --> 05:48.931
Are you trying to be funny or what?

05:50.099 --> 05:51.517
Isn't he funny, Jun?

05:52.143 --> 05:53.436
Dad.

05:53.519 --> 05:57.857
Does my hair look better
when it's to the side or up?

05:57.940 --> 05:59.150
-Let me see.
-All right.

05:59.233 --> 06:01.944
-This way?
-Come closer.

06:02.028 --> 06:03.237
Number one.

06:03.321 --> 06:04.572
Number two.

06:04.655 --> 06:06.699
-I don't know, you prick.
-Seriously?

06:06.783 --> 06:08.242
Just come home early.

06:08.326 --> 06:09.619
Don't go around causing trouble.

06:09.702 --> 06:10.620
Fine.

06:11.954 --> 06:12.997
I'm going out then.

06:13.081 --> 06:14.665
Good luck on your date, Dad.

06:14.749 --> 06:16.167
Be quiet, you little…

06:16.250 --> 06:17.418
A date?

06:18.169 --> 06:19.045
Hey.

06:19.128 --> 06:21.631
-Is your dad going on a date?
-Yes.

06:40.858 --> 06:41.859
Hey, Jae-hun.

06:41.943 --> 06:43.361
You came up first!

06:43.444 --> 06:44.779
Where's Dae-bum?

06:47.240 --> 06:48.950
Dae-bum is amazing!

06:49.033 --> 06:50.493
He's so great at this.

06:50.576 --> 06:51.661
Let's go back in again.

07:02.964 --> 07:04.674
Dae-bum, you came up already?

07:04.757 --> 07:08.261
Dae-bum is more impatient than I thought.

07:08.344 --> 07:10.471
He's in last place!

07:11.722 --> 07:12.890
I'm so out of breath.

07:13.975 --> 07:16.227
The last place gets splashed!

07:16.310 --> 07:17.687
Time for punishment!

07:17.770 --> 07:19.272
-Gosh.
-Come here!

07:21.941 --> 07:23.609
Heads up, Yeo-reum.

07:27.947 --> 07:29.907
Stop it!

07:29.991 --> 07:31.159
Hey!

07:31.242 --> 07:32.910
I'm sorry.

07:32.994 --> 07:34.162
Take this!

07:34.245 --> 07:36.205
It went into my eyes!

07:39.750 --> 07:41.711
-You brought a ukulele?
-Ta-da.

07:41.794 --> 07:43.546
When did you bring that?

07:44.088 --> 07:46.215
Music always accompanies vacations.

07:46.299 --> 07:47.383
Are you any good?

07:47.467 --> 07:48.551
-Yeo-reum.
-I'm quite good.

07:48.634 --> 07:49.886
-Really?
-Have a peach.

07:50.803 --> 07:53.473
I'm sorry. I should have washed it.

07:53.556 --> 07:54.932
-Here's a soft one.
-Everyone.

07:55.016 --> 07:56.100
I love soft peaches!

07:56.184 --> 07:57.393
-Guys?
-Yes?

07:57.894 --> 07:59.353
Shall we enjoy some music now?

07:59.437 --> 08:00.813
Let me see you perform first.

08:05.359 --> 08:07.028
He's quite good.

08:09.238 --> 08:13.242
Spring is here

08:13.826 --> 08:16.704
-Spring is here
-What the heck?

08:16.787 --> 08:18.706
-I'm happy
-You lovebirds.

08:18.789 --> 08:19.957
What do you mean?

08:20.041 --> 08:21.584
-To be
-Look at you smiling.

08:21.667 --> 08:24.337
With you

08:25.796 --> 08:27.340
Yeo-reum, sing along.

08:27.423 --> 08:30.384
-Summer is here
-…here

08:30.468 --> 08:31.385
Summer is…

08:31.469 --> 08:34.847
-Here
-Here

08:34.931 --> 08:36.807
-Dae-bum's turn. Dae-bum is
-Dae-bum is

08:36.891 --> 08:39.310
-Here
-Here

08:39.393 --> 08:41.437
-Dae-bum is here
-Dae-bum is blushing!

08:42.647 --> 08:44.565
-Are you blushing, Dae-bum?
-He's really good.

08:44.649 --> 08:45.691
-Yeo-reum, get up!
-Sing with me.

08:45.775 --> 08:46.901
We are

08:47.485 --> 08:49.612
-Here
-You should get up too, Dae-bum.

08:49.695 --> 08:53.533
I'm happy that

08:53.616 --> 08:57.453
-we are here together
-we are here together

08:59.413 --> 09:01.374
Round of applause, please.

09:02.041 --> 09:03.876
That was great.

09:03.960 --> 09:05.253
Hold on, that's not fair.

09:05.336 --> 09:06.337
I want a peach too.

09:07.672 --> 09:08.589
-Gosh!
-Hey!

09:08.673 --> 09:09.507
Watch out.

09:24.313 --> 09:25.439
You…

09:27.358 --> 09:28.192
What?

09:28.985 --> 09:29.986
Do I look sharp?

09:31.320 --> 09:32.738
Why do you look like that?

09:33.364 --> 09:34.699
Just say that you like it.

09:34.782 --> 09:36.158
I don't know where to begin.

09:37.201 --> 09:38.911
What are we having? I'm hungry.

09:38.995 --> 09:40.204
Actually,

09:40.288 --> 09:44.500
I've called Angok Garden ahead of time
and told them to get a big carp ready.

09:44.584 --> 09:47.211
It's too hot for that.
Let's just go somewhere nearby.

09:47.295 --> 09:49.213
Hey, come on.

09:49.297 --> 09:51.424
I'm buying you a meal to cheer you up,

09:51.507 --> 09:53.718
so we should at least have braised carp.

09:55.052 --> 09:56.345
Are you wearing cologne?

09:58.514 --> 10:00.891
Why? Does it smell nice?

10:00.975 --> 10:02.977
-Wait here, I'll get my car keys.
-Hold on.

10:03.603 --> 10:06.314
Let me take you on my bike today.

10:07.648 --> 10:09.609
We're not some high schoolers!

10:09.692 --> 10:12.778
Come on, this will bring back
memories back from high school.

10:12.862 --> 10:15.281
-Gosh.
-Hurry, wear this.

10:15.364 --> 10:17.074
For goodness' sake.

10:17.742 --> 10:20.995
I'm just too embarrassed
to be on the motorcycle with you.

10:21.078 --> 10:22.246
Hop on.

10:22.872 --> 10:24.165
I can't believe this.

10:24.248 --> 10:25.750
You have to hold on tightly.

10:26.667 --> 10:28.169
Or you'll fall off.

10:28.252 --> 10:29.670
Were you on a blind date?

10:29.754 --> 10:31.255
Blind date, my foot.

10:31.339 --> 10:33.090
It's just a happy occasion.

10:33.174 --> 10:34.967
You're wearing too much cologne, idiot!

10:35.051 --> 10:35.968
Hold on tight.

10:36.886 --> 10:38.095
I said hold on tight!

10:45.019 --> 10:47.271
You got all dressed up for me today.

10:48.481 --> 10:49.982
I wear this all the time.

10:51.233 --> 10:53.361
-The view is so nice!
-Will you keep it down?

10:53.444 --> 10:56.155
Why are you being like this?
Let's just go quietly.

10:56.697 --> 10:57.740
How do you like this?

10:57.823 --> 10:59.158
It's nature's air-conditioning!

11:01.285 --> 11:02.745
It's nice, okay?

11:06.040 --> 11:08.167
I'm all you've got, right?

11:10.252 --> 11:11.337
Whatever.

11:11.420 --> 11:13.672
-"Whatever."
-Seriously.

11:14.715 --> 11:16.300
Let's go have something good!

11:26.560 --> 11:27.895
I really don't get it.

11:28.479 --> 11:30.314
What is his intention?

11:30.398 --> 11:31.440
Tell me.

11:32.733 --> 11:33.567
Yeo-reum.

11:34.735 --> 11:36.987
Don't you want to
experience this just once?

11:37.071 --> 11:39.156
No. Definitely not.

11:41.367 --> 11:42.284
Dae-bum.

11:42.368 --> 11:43.786
What about you?

11:43.869 --> 11:45.621
I think I'll pass.

11:47.081 --> 11:48.833
Gosh, seriously. Look at us.

11:48.916 --> 11:51.460
I was so happy
when he mentioned Korean chicken.

11:51.544 --> 11:52.545
Tell me about it.

11:53.379 --> 11:54.922
I didn't know it was a live one.

11:57.508 --> 11:59.009
I'm starving.

11:59.093 --> 12:00.136
Let's just kill it.

12:00.719 --> 12:01.554
But who will?

12:02.430 --> 12:04.473
-Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!
-That's so sudden!

12:04.557 --> 12:06.559
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

12:08.310 --> 12:10.354
-Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!
-Hey.

12:11.147 --> 12:12.898
-Oh, no!
-It's you.

12:14.400 --> 12:16.110
Hurry up, Bom.

12:16.193 --> 12:18.237
-It's all yours.
-No!

12:22.908 --> 12:24.034
That looks so good.

12:31.584 --> 12:32.668
This is so good.

12:35.296 --> 12:37.089
I was going to add some eggs,

12:39.091 --> 12:41.385
-but it kept staring at me.
-Good job.

12:41.469 --> 12:44.889
I think cooking it in the caldron
made it even better.

12:46.140 --> 12:47.183
It's good, right?

12:47.766 --> 12:50.311
I told you I make great ramyeon
when we first met.

12:51.020 --> 12:52.021
How is it, Dae-bum?

12:55.483 --> 12:56.734
It's so delicious.

13:01.113 --> 13:02.323
I'm so full.

13:02.865 --> 13:04.283
That was a good meal.

13:04.366 --> 13:05.993
I'm glad you all enjoyed the ramyeon,

13:06.577 --> 13:08.078
but what was all that work for?

13:08.162 --> 13:09.455
Hey.

13:09.538 --> 13:12.458
Think about why
we had to work at the grove.

13:19.965 --> 13:21.050
Hello?

13:22.468 --> 13:23.552
Right now?

13:24.261 --> 13:27.097
I thought he was going to bring it
in the morning.

13:27.681 --> 13:29.642
-Okay.
-What is it?

13:29.725 --> 13:30.768
Who was that?

13:31.310 --> 13:34.355
It's the bus company. They're bringing
the luggage to the station.

13:34.438 --> 13:35.898
-Right now?
-Yes.

13:35.981 --> 13:37.149
Why now?

13:37.233 --> 13:38.901
We just finished our dinner.

13:38.984 --> 13:40.653
-I know, right?
-It's okay.

13:40.736 --> 13:43.280
We'll have a feast tomorrow morning.

13:44.365 --> 13:45.574
Should we go together?

13:46.700 --> 13:48.327
No. It's fine.

13:48.410 --> 13:49.328
Let's go, Bom.

13:50.371 --> 13:51.539
Seriously.

13:52.456 --> 13:55.251
Clean up for us, okay? See you.

13:55.334 --> 13:56.335
Bye.

13:56.418 --> 13:57.795
Stay safe.

14:06.178 --> 14:07.263
Bom.

14:08.097 --> 14:10.140
-Yes?
-It's nice.

14:12.768 --> 14:14.103
What is?

14:14.186 --> 14:18.023
Just the fact that
we're the only two here in this darkness.

14:18.691 --> 14:20.025
Cut it out already.

14:21.527 --> 14:24.321
When is the bus coming?
Is it even on its way here?

14:26.073 --> 14:29.034
I've been really happy
ever since I met you.

14:30.202 --> 14:31.161
Hey.

14:31.245 --> 14:32.580
Be honest with me.

14:32.663 --> 14:34.748
They sent you back to Korea
because you talked too much, right?

14:35.457 --> 14:36.542
It's the opposite.

14:37.751 --> 14:41.338
Everyone made fun of me
because I couldn't speak English.

14:41.422 --> 14:42.923
So I was quiet the whole time.

14:44.466 --> 14:46.051
When did you go to the States?

14:47.052 --> 14:48.596
Back when I was in the sixth grade.

14:49.221 --> 14:52.182
So you came back to Korea
because your English didn't improve?

14:52.266 --> 14:53.392
No.

14:53.475 --> 14:56.520
My English improved as time went by.

14:57.938 --> 14:59.899
But when I pronounced something wrong,

14:59.982 --> 15:01.775
they made fun of me
for being an Asian kid.

15:03.193 --> 15:04.862
I couldn't put up with it at one point.

15:04.945 --> 15:07.323
-So I beat someone up.
-What?

15:07.907 --> 15:08.741
You did?

15:12.202 --> 15:14.622
That's when my parents realized
how serious this was

15:14.705 --> 15:15.956
and sent me back here.

15:17.207 --> 15:19.418
Your parents must have been upset.

15:20.878 --> 15:21.962
Not really.

15:22.963 --> 15:25.090
I'm sure they're happy that I'm gone.

15:26.383 --> 15:27.801
They're ashamed of me.

15:29.178 --> 15:30.971
They're both extremely smart.

15:31.680 --> 15:33.349
But I'm the only dumb one.

15:37.102 --> 15:39.855
They're both renowned professors
in psychology,

15:42.441 --> 15:44.193
but they don't know how I feel.

15:51.450 --> 15:52.618
The bus is here.

15:52.701 --> 15:53.577
Let's go.

16:00.834 --> 16:02.920
Hello. I'm here for the luggage.

16:04.588 --> 16:06.048
There it is.

16:06.131 --> 16:07.883
Look how plump it is.

16:08.467 --> 16:09.677
Let me debone it for you.

16:10.761 --> 16:11.804
Stop.

16:12.304 --> 16:14.014
I'll do it for you.

16:14.848 --> 16:17.017
-Isn't that the innards?
-No, it's the meat.

16:17.101 --> 16:18.560
Try it with rice.

16:24.233 --> 16:25.150
It's good.

16:26.610 --> 16:29.279
You won't get dishes like this in Seoul.

16:29.363 --> 16:31.156
Have as much as you want.

16:31.657 --> 16:32.658
Thanks.

16:36.370 --> 16:38.205
Here, you love this.

16:38.872 --> 16:39.707
Makgeolli.

16:40.791 --> 16:42.209
You shouldn't drink.

16:42.292 --> 16:44.294
I never drink.

16:51.135 --> 16:52.261
So…

16:53.137 --> 16:54.096
Ji-yeong.

16:55.055 --> 16:58.475
I asked you out for dinner today because…

17:03.063 --> 17:04.023
What is it?

17:04.523 --> 17:05.441
You know,

17:05.524 --> 17:08.736
it's not easy for a man and a woman
to just stay as friends.

17:08.819 --> 17:10.654
But look how many years we've lasted.

17:14.158 --> 17:15.159
And…

17:15.951 --> 17:16.952
Well…

17:18.829 --> 17:19.788
Ji-yeong.

17:22.499 --> 17:24.334
-I…
-Seong-man.

17:25.711 --> 17:27.755
Can I ask you a favor as a friend?

17:29.214 --> 17:30.340
Of course.

17:30.841 --> 17:33.719
Ask away. I'll do anything for you.

17:34.970 --> 17:36.430
Can you please kick that lady

17:37.347 --> 17:38.724
out of your building?

17:39.933 --> 17:41.268
Who? Yeo-reum?

17:43.353 --> 17:45.355
What? Why all of a sudden?

17:45.939 --> 17:47.858
Yeo-reum is a decent person.

17:48.692 --> 17:49.777
What makes her decent?

17:51.653 --> 17:54.156
The way she quit her job
to laze around all day?

17:54.239 --> 17:55.491
Do you also find that charming?

17:55.574 --> 17:58.118
What do you mean? I didn't--

17:58.202 --> 18:02.623
That's called being
irresponsible and incapable.

18:03.207 --> 18:05.250
I want to live a life like that too.

18:05.334 --> 18:09.755
Many people put up with their hardships
and fight to live on.

18:09.838 --> 18:12.925
-Don't you think so?
-Yes, you're right.

18:13.008 --> 18:15.344
And I don't care if she lives like that.

18:15.427 --> 18:17.513
But she's a bad influence
to people around her.

18:21.350 --> 18:24.311
Did Yeo-reum say something to you?

18:28.774 --> 18:29.900
Dae-bum…

18:31.485 --> 18:33.737
keeps changing because of her.

18:43.163 --> 18:44.832
Wait, Ji-yeong…

18:47.000 --> 18:48.710
when you were crying the other time…

18:50.587 --> 18:52.589
Dae-bum changed too much.

18:59.680 --> 19:01.014
What do I do?

19:03.600 --> 19:05.477
I think I like Dae-bum.

19:30.502 --> 19:32.671
-Bom.
-Yes?

19:34.923 --> 19:37.467
Do you know
when I started falling for you?

19:38.510 --> 19:41.471
Stop it. You're making me cringe.

19:44.057 --> 19:45.934
When I got assigned to your class…

20:01.366 --> 20:03.285
Even here, they made fun of me

20:03.368 --> 20:06.121
saying I rolled my tongue
and tried to show off.

20:06.747 --> 20:09.291
I thought, "it's the same in Korea."

20:09.374 --> 20:10.834
Keep your voices down.

20:11.418 --> 20:14.087
I felt like there was no place
for me here either.

20:16.131 --> 20:18.175
Then I started hating myself.

20:19.343 --> 20:21.887
Who would love me
when even my own parents don't?

20:22.888 --> 20:25.307
I realized that racism
wasn't the problem in the US.

20:25.390 --> 20:26.475
I was.

20:26.558 --> 20:28.268
Keep it down.

20:28.352 --> 20:29.770
I was to blame.

20:36.360 --> 20:38.570
So I only listened to music during recess.

20:41.490 --> 20:43.158
I ran away like I wasn't interested.

21:07.432 --> 21:09.434
So this is what you always listen to.

21:11.687 --> 21:12.980
It's not bad.

21:14.940 --> 21:16.024
And…

21:16.858 --> 21:19.528
you were the first person
to come and talk to me.

21:20.487 --> 21:22.698
Although you might not remember.

21:55.564 --> 21:57.357
When I'm with you,

21:58.025 --> 22:00.819
it's nice that I don't have to
talk so much.

22:04.364 --> 22:06.241
It's the opposite for me.

22:08.035 --> 22:09.661
When I'm with you,

22:10.370 --> 22:12.164
I tend to talk more.

22:16.460 --> 22:19.171
Ever since I was young,

22:20.047 --> 22:22.591
talking to someone

22:23.342 --> 22:25.385
always felt like a burden to me.

22:33.143 --> 22:34.227
Dae-bum.

22:37.689 --> 22:40.067
Ever since the other night,

22:41.693 --> 22:44.154
there's something that's been
weighing on my mind.

22:46.948 --> 22:49.493
If only I didn't quit my job.

22:51.078 --> 22:53.080
If only I didn't come here for the sea.

22:55.540 --> 22:57.751
If only I didn't enter that library.

23:03.548 --> 23:05.675
If only I didn't move into
the billiard club.

23:08.470 --> 23:10.597
If any one of those didn't happen,

23:11.765 --> 23:14.351
you wouldn't have had to
go through all this.

23:18.188 --> 23:20.440
If only any one of those didn't happen…

23:31.660 --> 23:33.036
When you…

23:34.246 --> 23:36.081
first came to Angok,

23:37.541 --> 23:39.376
when you came to the library

23:40.460 --> 23:43.505
to make a membership card,
saying that you moved here,

23:45.006 --> 23:49.344
when we spent the night in the library,

23:50.637 --> 23:51.471
and…

23:52.264 --> 23:53.473
when I took you home

23:54.850 --> 23:56.977
when you were completely wasted…

23:58.478 --> 23:59.563
That's…

23:59.646 --> 24:02.399
When we had ice cream together
on the library bench,

24:03.692 --> 24:06.444
when we went to interview
the old lady together,

24:07.028 --> 24:08.071
and…

24:09.281 --> 24:12.409
when we went for a jog together
in the morning…

24:13.827 --> 24:16.037
I was happy.

24:19.374 --> 24:20.500
I'm…

24:22.586 --> 24:24.546
truly happy…

24:26.423 --> 24:28.300
that you came to Angok.

24:53.366 --> 24:54.576
It's raining.

24:59.706 --> 25:00.999
Hey, it's raining.

25:02.042 --> 25:03.293
Let's just walk.

25:04.002 --> 25:05.170
In this rain?

25:05.712 --> 25:06.796
Yes.

25:08.340 --> 25:09.341
Sure.

25:10.175 --> 25:11.801
It's nice and cool.

25:22.687 --> 25:24.439
I remember.

25:24.522 --> 25:25.482
What?

25:27.901 --> 25:29.319
I remember too.

25:32.322 --> 25:34.783
Did you really think
I wouldn't remember that day?

26:15.991 --> 26:17.200
Thank you for the food.

26:17.993 --> 26:19.244
I called a cab.

26:23.581 --> 26:25.208
You can't ride your bike in this rain.

26:25.292 --> 26:26.251
Take the cab with me.

26:26.334 --> 26:28.670
It's not my first time on a bike.

26:28.753 --> 26:30.547
You still shouldn't ride it in the rain.

26:31.464 --> 26:33.758
-Just take the cab with me.
-It's here.

26:36.803 --> 26:38.054
Come on.

26:38.638 --> 26:40.348
-Go in first.
-Gosh.

26:40.849 --> 26:42.642
-Ji-yeong, I'll see you later.
-Hey!

26:42.726 --> 26:44.561
-Sir, go ahead.
-Hey, get in!

27:07.917 --> 27:09.002
I've…

27:10.503 --> 27:13.089
always liked being in the rain
since I was young.

27:13.673 --> 27:15.925
I used to never use an umbrella.

27:34.361 --> 27:36.654
I heard about Bom's hospital bills.

27:41.910 --> 27:43.995
I heard about what happened in Seoul too.

27:52.921 --> 27:56.299
It's too good of an opportunity
to pass up.

28:08.728 --> 28:09.896
Yeo-reum.

28:13.525 --> 28:16.152
Do you want me to go to Seoul?

28:22.450 --> 28:23.493
Yes.

28:55.191 --> 28:58.236
I never used an umbrella as a kid

28:58.820 --> 29:00.405
just like you.

29:43.865 --> 29:46.201
We have fresh shrimp here!

29:46.284 --> 29:47.535
Discount only for today.

29:47.619 --> 29:49.829
Hello, sir. Don't you want some shrimp?

29:50.538 --> 29:53.082
Are you sure? It's really delicious today.

29:53.166 --> 29:54.667
It's in season right now.

29:54.751 --> 29:57.253
-Thank you.
-He's good at that.

29:57.837 --> 30:00.423
-Do you want some shrimp?
-Are you working like this every day?

30:00.507 --> 30:02.091
No.

30:02.175 --> 30:04.260
-I'm off on Mondays.
-Are you sure you don't want any?

30:04.344 --> 30:07.013
-It'll be hot in the summer though.
-Thank you.

30:07.096 --> 30:09.516
Do you prefer this over waiting tables?

30:09.599 --> 30:10.433
-I do.
-Thank you.

30:10.517 --> 30:11.810
-It pays more.
-Discount today.

30:11.893 --> 30:13.853
Sir, do you want some shrimp?

30:13.937 --> 30:15.313
Gosh, you're so cool.

30:15.396 --> 30:16.314
Yes, ma'am.

30:16.397 --> 30:17.857
Oh, right.

30:17.941 --> 30:19.025
Thank you.

30:20.193 --> 30:22.904
I found them at a good price,
so I bought them for you.

30:22.987 --> 30:25.031
You really don't want some?
It's delicious.

30:25.114 --> 30:27.200
I'm not going to draw anymore though.

30:27.283 --> 30:29.244
Whatever. Just keep it.

30:29.327 --> 30:30.912
We have fresh shrimp!

30:31.704 --> 30:34.332
-Shrimp is here!
-Jae-hun is a natural.

30:34.415 --> 30:35.792
-Some shrimp?
-Yes.

30:35.875 --> 30:37.794
Are you sure he won't take your job?

30:38.962 --> 30:39.796
Thank you.

30:40.338 --> 30:41.631
Jae-hun!

30:42.298 --> 30:43.883
That's enough.

30:43.967 --> 30:45.009
Give it back now.

30:46.386 --> 30:47.428
Give it back!

30:47.512 --> 30:49.305
-I don't want to.
-Give it to me.

30:49.389 --> 30:52.183
Hey, give it.

30:53.643 --> 30:55.019
-Stop.
-What the heck?

30:55.103 --> 30:56.104
Hello?

30:56.187 --> 30:57.230
Hey!

30:57.897 --> 31:00.942
"I've been eating well here

31:01.025 --> 31:02.944
and working out every day."

31:03.027 --> 31:04.487
"I'm much better now."

31:06.239 --> 31:08.783
"Looking back with a clear mind,

31:10.535 --> 31:12.453
I felt so bad for the kids

31:13.246 --> 31:14.581
and you, Mom."

31:16.457 --> 31:19.127
"Mom, you've worked tirelessly
all your life."

31:19.752 --> 31:21.296
"My poor mother."

31:23.339 --> 31:26.467
"I'll be good to you when I'm home."

31:28.052 --> 31:31.389
"Please give my regards
to Bom and Ha-neul for me."

31:43.318 --> 31:44.402
Jeong-hun.

31:46.070 --> 31:48.197
Just stay healthy, okay?

31:50.700 --> 31:51.826
I'm sorry…

31:52.327 --> 31:54.454
for calling you
and asking you to read this.

31:54.537 --> 31:55.580
It's fine.

31:57.540 --> 31:59.667
Don't tell Bom about this, okay?

32:00.668 --> 32:01.669
You know,

32:02.170 --> 32:04.714
I think she'll be happy
to read this letter.

32:06.174 --> 32:07.175
Could I…

32:08.676 --> 32:10.845
Could I ask you for another favor?

32:12.013 --> 32:13.389
What is it?

32:15.767 --> 32:18.144
This is a bit embarrassing, but…

32:19.270 --> 32:21.314
Come on. What is it?

32:24.275 --> 32:25.276
Yeo-reum.

32:27.487 --> 32:29.697
Is it difficult
to learn how to read and write?

32:32.367 --> 32:33.576
I want to…

32:35.536 --> 32:39.165
reply to my son to tell him I'm well.

32:50.802 --> 32:52.428
This is so much better.

32:53.179 --> 32:55.890
You might get a heat stroke
wearing that shrimp costume.

32:55.974 --> 32:57.100
Can't you do something else?

32:57.684 --> 32:59.227
They don't even pay you much.

33:01.562 --> 33:03.898
What? What did you just say?

33:04.524 --> 33:06.317
I was just worried because it's hot.

33:06.401 --> 33:07.735
Heo Jae-hun.

33:07.819 --> 33:10.697
I don't know how much money
is good enough for you,

33:10.780 --> 33:12.657
but that money is important to me.

33:14.075 --> 33:16.035
Bom, I'm sorry. It was a slip of a tongue.

33:22.083 --> 33:23.251
Did that scare you?

33:24.335 --> 33:25.294
What?

33:25.920 --> 33:28.798
I'm asking if you're scared, you idiot.

33:29.465 --> 33:30.675
What, seriously?

33:30.758 --> 33:32.051
You caught me off guard.

33:34.512 --> 33:37.765
I feel like the world is collapsing
when you're angry at me.

33:39.475 --> 33:40.893
Collapsing, my foot.

33:42.103 --> 33:43.771
I want to go on a trip again.

33:45.064 --> 33:45.940
Same here.

33:46.941 --> 33:48.151
It was nice.

33:48.860 --> 33:49.986
Hey.

33:50.737 --> 33:52.238
What's with that creepy smile?

33:54.866 --> 33:55.992
You know what.

33:56.075 --> 33:58.828
What's wrong with you? Have you lost it?

33:59.579 --> 34:02.290
Bom. It's too late to back out.

34:02.874 --> 34:05.126
What do you mean it's too late?

34:05.626 --> 34:07.462
Bom, wait.

34:07.545 --> 34:08.838
Don't follow me.

34:09.547 --> 34:11.466
Then you click here.

34:11.549 --> 34:13.718
You print these out so you can label them.

34:13.801 --> 34:15.636
You enter the data here first,

34:15.720 --> 34:17.263
and these will get arranged.

34:18.139 --> 34:19.766
You enter the title of the book.

34:19.849 --> 34:21.392
And then its number.

34:21.476 --> 34:23.269
You finish that first,

34:23.811 --> 34:26.147
-and you glue these here.
-Right.

34:26.230 --> 34:29.067
All the information is here.
The rest is just manual labor.

34:32.153 --> 34:33.321
LITERATURE

34:33.404 --> 34:34.363
Yeo-reum.

34:35.865 --> 34:37.408
-Hello.
-Hello.

34:38.785 --> 34:41.829
About our morning jog…

34:43.706 --> 34:44.874
You weren't there.

34:48.086 --> 34:49.087
I…

34:50.963 --> 34:52.173
My sneakers…

34:53.508 --> 34:55.843
My sneakers got torn.

34:59.097 --> 35:01.182
I don't think
I'll be able to jog for a while.

35:01.724 --> 35:02.850
I see.

35:07.146 --> 35:08.481
And also…

35:11.150 --> 35:12.944
I'm going to Seoul tomorrow.

35:15.071 --> 35:16.114
I see.

35:19.075 --> 35:21.077
That's good news.

35:22.495 --> 35:24.914
-Right.
-I'm sure you'll do well.

35:27.750 --> 35:28.668
Hey, Part-timer!

35:29.377 --> 35:31.754
Tell me where the library storage is.

35:31.838 --> 35:33.506
Give me a second.

35:34.090 --> 35:36.050
The storage is outside.

35:36.592 --> 35:39.095
-It's outside?
-I'll show you where it is.

35:40.346 --> 35:41.889
I'll be right back, ma'am.

36:01.075 --> 36:02.034
Yeo-reum.

36:04.829 --> 36:05.830
Thank you.

36:09.667 --> 36:10.668
Sure.

36:44.368 --> 36:46.412
This feels nice, doesn't it?

36:47.205 --> 36:51.918
You look like a proper city dog
now that you've taken a bath.

36:52.001 --> 36:54.003
You're so cute.

36:56.255 --> 36:57.465
All right.

37:00.676 --> 37:02.511
What else is there to do?

37:03.012 --> 37:05.014
Should I clean the bathroom?

37:41.300 --> 37:42.551
Does that hurt?

37:43.552 --> 37:45.263
Answer me!

37:48.057 --> 37:49.392
The person you are trying to reach…

37:49.475 --> 37:51.310
-is currently unavailable.
-He never picks up when I need him.

37:52.645 --> 37:54.146
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

37:54.689 --> 37:56.399
I don't know the exact size,

37:56.482 --> 37:58.234
but he's an eight-year-old boy.

37:58.317 --> 38:00.319
He's a bit chubby.

38:00.861 --> 38:04.865
For an 8-year-old,
the usual size is 120 to 130.

38:05.783 --> 38:10.121
But considering how fast kids grow,
size 140 would be the best.

38:15.501 --> 38:17.920
Do you have that size right now?

38:18.462 --> 38:20.381
Give me a moment. I'll go check.

38:27.138 --> 38:28.306
In life,

38:29.223 --> 38:32.184
there are people I like
and people I dislike.

38:36.731 --> 38:40.192
I can't do anything about that.

38:45.531 --> 38:46.574
But the thing is,

38:47.158 --> 38:50.077
when I dislike someone,
that's the end of it.

38:51.579 --> 38:52.872
It's those I like

38:54.248 --> 38:57.418
that end up making me sad.

39:01.672 --> 39:02.715
Come here.

39:05.760 --> 39:09.805
Those who have broken my heart

39:11.265 --> 39:15.061
were the ones that I loved dearly.

39:21.317 --> 39:23.110
I felt just as sad

39:24.195 --> 39:27.239
as how much I liked them.

39:28.824 --> 39:29.867
And now…

39:31.118 --> 39:34.330
I'm afraid to love anyone.

39:40.419 --> 39:41.545
I don't want

39:42.338 --> 39:45.007
any more sadness in my life.

40:10.574 --> 40:12.368
I'm being such a drama queen.

40:19.291 --> 40:20.876
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

40:40.813 --> 40:41.897
Dae-bum.

40:44.692 --> 40:45.776
Dae-bum.

40:45.860 --> 40:46.986
Dae-bum.

40:47.987 --> 40:48.988
Yeo-reum.

40:53.159 --> 40:54.869
There you are.

40:54.952 --> 40:56.912
What brings you here?

40:59.707 --> 41:00.708
Actually…

41:07.423 --> 41:08.632
I wanted to wish you

41:09.800 --> 41:11.927
a safe trip to Seoul and back home.

41:13.971 --> 41:15.014
Pardon?

41:17.683 --> 41:18.767
I wish you…

41:20.895 --> 41:22.396
a safe trip to Seoul

41:23.063 --> 41:24.398
and back home.

41:32.573 --> 41:33.949
I'll be back safe and sound.

41:39.246 --> 41:40.289
You know…

41:42.917 --> 41:46.337
I didn't cancel the movie tickets yet.

41:52.218 --> 41:53.344
Yeo-reum.

41:55.596 --> 41:56.430
Here.

41:57.306 --> 41:58.224
Take these.

41:59.475 --> 42:00.976
What's this?

42:01.060 --> 42:02.311
They're sneakers.

42:02.895 --> 42:05.731
You said your shoes got torn earlier.

42:06.815 --> 42:08.275
But I'm not sure about the size…

42:11.070 --> 42:12.404
Wait, your shoes are…

42:13.572 --> 42:14.865
just fine.

42:17.326 --> 42:18.410
You're right.

42:20.496 --> 42:22.540
They became fine.

42:24.959 --> 42:28.128
Then please jog on my behalf
while I'm gone.

42:30.506 --> 42:31.632
Okay.

42:55.698 --> 42:56.740
Summer…

42:58.742 --> 42:59.785
is so nice.

43:14.633 --> 43:17.386
A LIBRARY WITH A HAPPY LIFE
AND A BRIGHT FUTURE

43:23.309 --> 43:27.354
In the very corner of the library,
toward the left side,

43:27.438 --> 43:29.648
you'll see another seat.

43:30.691 --> 43:33.235
That's my favorite seat.

43:43.329 --> 43:45.956
I can't believe he kept
this great spot all to himself.

43:55.716 --> 43:56.675
Hello.

43:56.759 --> 43:57.843
-Thank you for coming.
-Hello.

43:57.926 --> 43:58.886
It's nothing.

43:58.969 --> 44:00.721
-Go ahead, Dae-bum. I'll go park the car.
-Okay.

44:00.804 --> 44:02.097
-Come to the third floor.
-Okay.

44:02.723 --> 44:04.600
Professor Lee is already there. Let's go.

44:04.683 --> 44:08.520
Just relax and tell them what happened.

44:22.159 --> 44:23.243
It's here.

44:35.506 --> 44:36.507
I'm sorry

44:37.091 --> 44:38.342
for calling you here.

44:40.302 --> 44:41.345
All right, then.

44:41.428 --> 44:43.430
-You don't have to. I got it.
-It's fine.

44:43.514 --> 44:44.598
Gosh.

44:44.682 --> 44:46.892
So where's Bom?

44:46.975 --> 44:49.061
She must have gone to get changed.

44:50.104 --> 44:52.773
-You don't need to help. I got it.
-I'm almost done.

44:52.856 --> 44:53.899
Goodness.

44:54.483 --> 44:55.442
Hey.

44:55.526 --> 44:56.360
Bom.

44:57.152 --> 45:00.197
-See you.
-See you.

45:00.280 --> 45:01.240
Goodbye.

45:01.323 --> 45:03.325
That's an ice cream cake.
You guys can share it.

45:03.409 --> 45:05.452
Oh, my. Thank you.

45:05.536 --> 45:08.247
Hey, don't do stuff like that for her.

45:08.330 --> 45:10.207
It'll only make my job harder.

45:10.290 --> 45:11.959
Why? She seemed to like it.

45:14.044 --> 45:15.963
Why would you buy such an expensive cake?

45:16.839 --> 45:19.049
Because people like it
when they get nice things.

45:19.550 --> 45:20.759
Heo Jae-hun.

45:20.843 --> 45:22.594
Do you even know
how much I get paid a day?

45:23.262 --> 45:25.806
I'm sorry.
I'll get something cheaper next--

45:25.889 --> 45:26.974
-Hey!
-Hey!

45:27.850 --> 45:29.435
You almost hit us!

45:29.518 --> 45:30.561
Have you lost it?

45:30.644 --> 45:31.895
-Hey, be careful.
-Hey.

45:32.479 --> 45:34.731
-What's wrong with him?
-Maybe it's your bully's friend.

45:34.815 --> 45:35.691
What?

45:35.774 --> 45:37.734
Why would they drive a motorcycle?

45:38.694 --> 45:40.571
Hey, watch out!

45:40.654 --> 45:42.406
Who the hell are you? Do you want to die?

45:43.115 --> 45:44.741
-You must be insane.
-Hey.

45:44.825 --> 45:46.076
Hey, wait!

45:46.160 --> 45:47.536
Bom, move out!

46:00.674 --> 46:02.801
-Hey, Dae-ho!
-Bom!

46:04.219 --> 46:06.763
-When did you get released?
-Just now.

46:06.847 --> 46:09.224
I went to your grandma's,
and she told me you were here.

46:09.308 --> 46:10.142
Hey.

46:10.225 --> 46:12.436
You could have given me a heads-up.

46:12.519 --> 46:14.354
How could you not tell me? Come here.

46:14.438 --> 46:17.149
Wait. I think you've grown a bit taller.

46:17.232 --> 46:19.193
-I have?
-You've gotten so big.

46:19.276 --> 46:21.945
I haven't grown at all
since middle school.

46:22.029 --> 46:24.615
It seems like you've lost some weight.

46:24.698 --> 46:26.617
Well, I worked out a bit.

46:26.700 --> 46:28.827
-Hey, let go!
-What the heck is this?

46:28.911 --> 46:29.912
Get off her.

46:34.958 --> 46:36.043
Who's this guy?

46:37.461 --> 46:39.046
Oh, he's my…

46:39.129 --> 46:41.048
This guy is Bom's boyfriend.

46:41.632 --> 46:42.466
Well…

46:43.008 --> 46:44.051
Let go.

46:45.552 --> 46:47.888
I guess a lot has changed since then.

46:48.472 --> 46:50.891
So who are you?

46:50.974 --> 46:52.643
He's my best friend.

46:52.726 --> 46:53.977
My childhood friend.

46:54.061 --> 46:55.312
-Your best friend?
-Yes.

46:56.438 --> 46:57.856
Why is your best friend…

46:59.191 --> 47:00.651
We can introduce each other later.

47:00.734 --> 47:01.652
Kim Bom.

47:02.611 --> 47:04.196
Hey. Seriously.

47:05.364 --> 47:06.490
Let's hang out soon.

47:07.199 --> 47:08.867
Okay. Take care.

47:08.951 --> 47:10.160
And…

47:11.620 --> 47:12.871
your name is?

47:12.955 --> 47:14.373
It's Heo Jae-hun.

47:14.456 --> 47:16.208
All right. Good to see you too.

47:17.251 --> 47:19.127
-Drive safely.
-See you later.

47:19.211 --> 47:20.295
Bye.

47:22.339 --> 47:24.049
What's wrong with you?

47:27.261 --> 47:29.388
Come on, he's just a friend.

47:29.972 --> 47:32.224
Friends don't hug like that.

47:32.307 --> 47:33.642
It's because we're close.

47:33.725 --> 47:35.435
He's my best friend.

47:36.019 --> 47:37.646
Yes, you can come by today.

47:37.729 --> 47:38.939
BILLIARD CLUB

47:39.022 --> 47:40.399
I'll see you later.

47:43.360 --> 47:46.446
SEON-A BILLIARD CLUB

49:28.965 --> 49:31.051
The footage showed Geun-ho
running out from here.

49:31.134 --> 49:32.594
Did anything happen?

49:33.136 --> 49:36.973
You must be feeling uneasy
about telling him.

49:37.057 --> 49:40.394
It's like you know me
inside out, Ms. Jung.

49:40.477 --> 49:42.646
She's going to take my place
as your granddaughter. 

49:42.729 --> 49:44.898
You're here on a vacation, aren't you?

49:44.981 --> 49:47.901
Can't you just consider this something
that happened on your vacation?

49:47.984 --> 49:50.404
Please keep it a secret. I'm so sorry.

49:50.487 --> 49:51.655
Grandma.

49:51.738 --> 49:53.907
Where did she go with all the lights off?

49:55.409 --> 49:59.913
Subtitle translation by: Jea-Heon Chung
